<h2 id="motivation">Motivation</h2>

<p>I want to set up Hadoop, Spark, and Hive on my personal laptop.</p>

<h2 id="method">Method</h2>

<h3 id="installation">Installation</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Set up WSL following <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/install-win10">this guide</a>.</li>
  <li>Install Hadoop following <a href="https://kontext.tech/docs/DataAndBusinessIntelligence/p/install-hadoop-320-on-windows-10-using-windows-subsystem-for-linux-wsl">this guide</a>.</li>
  <li>Install Hive following <a href="https://kontext.tech/docs/DataAndBusinessIntelligence/p/apache-hive-311-installation-on-windows-10-using-windows-subsystem-for-linux">this guide</a>.</li>
  <li>Install Spark following <a href="https://kontext.tech/docs/DataAndBusinessIntelligence/p/apache-spark-243-installation-on-windows-10-using-windows-subsystem-for-linux">this guide</a>.</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="start">Start</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Open WSL terminal.</li>
  <li>Type
    <div class="language-sh highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>service ssh restart
<span class="nb">cd</span> <span class="nv">$HADOOP_HOME</span>
sbin/start-all.sh
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Open <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">http://localhost:8088/cluster</code> in browser to view resource manager. Note that only spark jobs submitted to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">yarn</code> will show up here.</li>
</ol>
:ET